post_text:
We are definitely living in a New World! Join the Pratt High School theatre department for lots of singing and dancing as we present "Songs for a New World" written by Jason Robert Brown.

Originally Produced by the WPA Theatre, New York City,1995 (Kyle Renick, Artistic Director). Original Orchestration by Brian Besterman and JasonRobert Brown.

We are excited to provide a special performance Sept. 11 at 9:30 am for our senior citizens and vulnerable population. Bring a mask and social distance with us.

Other performances are Sept. 12 at 7:30 pm and Sept. 13 at 2:00 pm at Liberty Middle School Auditorium. Tickets are $5. Masks will be required for entry. Seating is limited so reserved seating is recommended.

Contact Arica Malone at arica.malone@usd382.com to reserve seats.

Reminder that our PHS/LMS Football and Cheer Parents Meetings are tonight at 7 pm in the PHS gym. The east and west doors to Pratt High School will both be open.

The PHS/LMS Fall Sports Parents Meeting have been divided up by sport to help with Social Distancing and to provide opportunities to discuss KSHSAA Covid-19 mitigation protocols based upon the activity (inside, outside etc.). All meetings will start in the PHS Gym. Please wear a mask as Pratt County is under a mandatory mask order from our local health department. Seating in the gym is marked off every other row for social distancing.

Please come prepared to join the Pratt High School Booster Club and support your kids! Your support helps our Booster Club give thousands of dollars each year to our athletic programs.

Fall 2020 PHS/LMS Parents Meetings
Thursday, August 13 @ 7:00 pm. Football and Cheer @ PHS Gym
Monday, August 17 @ 7:00 pm. Volleyball @ PHS Gym
Tuesday, August 18 @ 7:00 pm. Cross Country, Golf and Tennis @ PHS Gym

post_text:
Fall Sports Practices are coming up quickly. PHS Fall coaches have contacted their athletes about attending the required KSHSAA Concussion Information sessions. We had good attendance at Cheer yesterday and Football today. Attendance is required before participating in a practice on Monday, August 17. Time for all Greenbacks to get this important detail accomplished.

PHS Fall Sport Athletes have two great options. They can come to an in-person session that lasts about twenty minutes or do the on-line option. The choice is yours. Both are attached below. Athletes only going out for Winter or Spring Sports will have Concussion Information sessions scheduled during Go-Time after school starts.

if not accomplished in advance, athletes from Football, Cross Country, and Volleyball may attend the August 17 3:45 p.m. session and join Golf and Tennis. However, that will necessitate missing part of practice on the first day.

post_text:
The County Commission passed a resolution this morning, July 3, exempting Pratt County from the mandatory Governor mask requirement; but at the same time highly encouraging masks.

USD 382 will require masks to be worn by coaches and athletes to enter the weight room Monday. There is not way to maintain any sort of social distancing within our work groups while effectively spotting on bench and squat etc. We must work to ensure the safety of all Greenback coaches and athletes based upon the best advice of medical experts.

Greenback coaches will have single use masks available on Monday for athletes unable to procure a mask by Monday.

Calling all Juniors (well, I guess technically you are now seniors 🙂
We need your help decorating for Saturday's Prom. The more help we have, the faster we can get it done! We can't start decorating until 12:00pm due to the Farmer's Market at Merchant Park in the morning. Please meet at Merchant Park at noon and be prepared to work for a couple of hours. We would like to have it all done by 4:00pm so you have plenty of time to get ready for the BIG EVENT! We will also need to have juniors stay after the dance for a short time to help take down the decorations.

Please email Meagan or Summer if you have any questions.

The PHS Booster Club Athletic Banquet scheduled for Monday, April 27 has been cancelled due to the COVID-19 pandemic. The Booster Club is planning an alternative way to honor Seniors and PHS Athletes. More information will follow in the future.

The Pratt High School All-Sports Program will be produced and a hard copy for Senior Parents will be in Senior Graduation Packets. Also, an On-line All Sports Program version will be available for the public later this spring.
The Senior Athletes of the Year, Senior Three-Sport Athletes and Scholarship WInners will still be announced at a to be determined date.

The PHS Faculty are busy this week getting ready to provide an on-line continuous learning opportunity for all PHS students Grades 9-12 starting Monday, May 30. In preparation for this, the PHS building will be open tomorrow on Wednesday, March 25 on a VERY LIMITED BASIS for students to retrieve needed personal articles out of their lockers. An E-MAIL WITH ALL DETAILS WAS SENT TO YOUR STUDENT. Please have your students read the e-mail and/or all information attached below before coming to the school.

It is very important we practice great social distancing to keep everyone safe, flatten the curve for the CO-VID-19 virus and thereby reduce the number of illness and deaths both locally and nation-wide.
